### who's it for?

This isn't limited in any way to a particular skill level or skill set. It
would be boring if everyone knew the same things, worked on the same projects,
and worked the same way. There won't be instructional time (tutorials or
classes) or handholding initially, so you'll have to find your own way into the
field if you're not already there. If you've never made anything remotely
related to art, code, or hardware, you'll probably want to do that first.

### when do we meet?

We will meet at least once a month to show what we've been working on, get
criticism and comment, and share our intentions. Something like [Hack and
Tell](http://hackandtell.org) meets [dorkbot](http://dorkbot.org) meets
[writers' workshop](http://www.mwabaltimore.org/). Outside of meetings we keep
in touch (that's what the internet is for) to encourage and push. We
communicate our work to the outside world through writing,
[prose](http://tumblr.com) and [code](http://github.com), and through
presentation of the things we make.

The first meeting is **Thursday, October 27 at 8:00 PM** at the [Baltimore
Node's space](http://baltimorenode.org), **120 W. North Ave, Baltimore MD.**
Location and date are fluid depending on who is interested and when they can
make it.

